<h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
<p>We strive to be a public house in the traditional sense, creating a community forum offering coffee, teas, libations and creative foods as an invitation to discussion and revolutionary ideas.</p>
<p>We believe in the principle: “Good enough is not good enough!”</p>
<p>The collective mission is to adhere to our values:</p>
<ul>
<li>Industry-based innovation</li>
<li>Community education of product and practices</li>
<li>Above-and-beyond service standards</li>
<li>Speed, but never at the expense of quality</li>
<li>Odds-defying consistancy</li>
</ul>
<p>Ante Meridiem. Post Meridiem. Timeless.</p>
<h2>Our Menu</h2>
<p>Our food menu is based on the desire to cater to our guests’ needs at every time of the day. We use the “Cold Kitchen” café standard, which foregoes the use of fire or fryer. This has allowed us to create dishes that require a fair amount of energy and thought. Each dish is our own special spin on classic fare.</p>
<p>We strive to create as much as we can in-house, from our famous dressings to our specialty simple syrups to liven up your coffee beverage, iced tea or adult concoction.</p>
<p>We are committed to working with local vendors whenever possible. We have partnered with many local small distributors and chefs to bring you something special.</p>
<p>We hope you love it!</p>
                                                
